This is a great idea. It will give us more room.<br><br>
JJ the Boonirat had a great story about his Vietnam Vet bumper sticker and the man who thanked him. My comments were:<br><br>
&quot;Your story of the bumper sticker is about the most wonderful thing I have heard in a long time. I am beginning to realize that there are people out there who care. I had a similar experience when I hung my decorations in my office four months ago. It was real tough to do that, and for a while people did not know what to say, but little by little the reactions were very much the opposite of my worst       fears. Being in &quot;exile&quot; for so long really takes its toll.&quot;<br><br>
I thought I was the only one in that state of mind. I never gave it a thought that there were others who were as isolated. I have come to realize that the self imposed exile of many of us was a very normal and very human reaction to some of our experiences. It was very difficult to overcome, and twinges from it still strongly linger. 
